// @test regression/unused-vars-sequence
// @description Variables inside comma-separated declarations (SequenceStatement) must be walked and collected: `base` is used in the first inner statement, `a`/`b` are declared by them. NOTE: no --tv probe has confirmed TV accepts this comma form (see plan/31 Finding 3 caveat) - this fixture asserts our analyzer is not blind to nodes our parser emits, not that the syntax is TV-valid.
// @expects parse: success
// @expects warnings: 0
//@version=6
indicator("x")
base = 10.0
a = base + 1, b = a * 2
plot(b)
